

---
const pageTitle = "Albedo";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>

    <style>
      :root {
        --paper: #ffffff;
        --ink: #000000;
        --line: #000000;
        --blue: #0000ee;
        --red: #cc0000;
        --green: #008000;
      }

      html, body {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      a { text-decoration: underline; }
      a.blue { color: var(--blue); }
      a.red { color: var(--red); }
      a.green { color: var(--green); }

      .page {
        width: min(900px, calc(100% - 48px));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 28px 0 60px;
      }

      .topbar {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 10px 14px;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
        text-align: center;
        background: #fafafa;
      }

      .frame {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 22px 24px 28px;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
        background:
          linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(255,255,255,0.96), rgba(245,245,245,0.96)),
          repeating-linear-gradient(
            to bottom,
            rgba(0,0,0,0.015) 0px,
            rgba(0,0,0,0.015) 1px,
            transparent 1px,
            transparent 4px
          );
      }

      .symbol-bg {
        position: absolute;
        top: 50%;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(3deg);
        width: 300px;
        height: 300px;
        opacity: 0.15;
        pointer-events: none;
        user-select: none;
      }

      .symbol-bg svg { width: 100%; height: 100%; }

      .content-layer { position: relative; z-index: 1; }

      h1 {
        font-size: 42px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 0 0 8px;
      }

      .subtitle {
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 15px;
        margin-bottom: 24px;
      }

      .quote {
        margin: 22px auto;
        max-width: 680px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 14px;
        background: #f3f3f3;
        font-style: italic;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .section-title {
        font-size: 28px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 30px 0 14px;
      }

      .mini-links { text-align: center; margin-top: 30px; }

      .footer-note {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 26px;
        font-size: 14px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="page">
      <div class="topbar">
        <span>[ <a class="blue" href="/">home</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="blue" href="/alchemy">alchemy index</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="green" href="/alchemy/nigredo">previous</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="red" href="/alchemy/rubedo">next</a> ]</span>
      </div>

      <main class="frame">
        <div class="symbol-bg">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 300 300" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <circle cx="150" cy="150" r="90" stroke="black" stroke-width="3"/>
            <circle cx="150" cy="150" r="40" stroke="black" stroke-width="3"/>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="content-layer">
          <h1>Albedo</h1>
          <p class="subtitle">alchemy / whitening / clarity / archive entry 002</p>

          <p>
            Albedo follows nigredo. After breakdown comes a stage of clearing,
            reflection, and emerging clarity. The confusion begins to settle,
            and something quieter starts to take shape.
          </p>

          <div class="quote">
            after the dark, something begins to be seen more clearly.
          </div>

          <h2 class="section-title">clarification</h2>
          <p>
            What was chaotic begins to organize. Not into a final form, but into
            something more understandable. Patterns appear where there was once
            only confusion.
          </p>

          <h2 class="section-title">reflection</h2>
          <p>
            Albedo carries a reflective quality. It is a stage of seeing, noticing,
            and becoming aware of what has been uncovered.
          </p>

          <h2 class="section-title">cooling</h2>
          <p>
            Where nigredo is heated and intense, albedo cools and clarifies. It
            allows distance, perspective, and a different kind of attention.
          </p>

          <div class="mini-links">
            <a class="blue" href="/alchemy">back to alchemy index</a>
            <a class="blue" href="/alchemy/rubedo">continue to: rubedo</a>
          </div>

          <p class="footer-note">this page is part of the hidden archive.</p>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>